",{"supplied":550},{"_":551,"reason":548},"ἔτη",[553,556],{"_":554,"ref":555},"❦","#ivy-leaf",{"_":554,"ref":555},{"type":558,"name":559},"attested","Ἀγαθόπου",[561,563],{"quantity":520,"unit":562},"character",{"quantity":520,"unit":562},{"gap":565},{"reason":548,"extent":566,"unit":562},"unknown",{"type":568,"resp":479,"listApp":569},"apparatus",{"app":570},[571,573,576],{"note":572},"Text from autopsy",{"loc":574,"note":575},"line 1","Castelli, Franz: Θ Κ; Ferrara: Θ Κ I; Kaibel Θ Κ Σ (i.e. Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοι)ς)",{"loc":577,"note":578},"line 4",{"_":579,"ref":580},"Franz: ἔζη[σας ἔτη]; Kaibel: ἔζη[σεν ἔτη]; Korhonen: ἔζη[σας ἔτη] (or ἔζη[σες ἔτη], frequent in Centuripe, see IG 14, no.578 = , IG 14, no.579 = , IG 14, no.581 = )",[581,584,587],{"_":582,"target":583},"ISic001397","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001397",{"_":585,"target":586},"ISic001398","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001398",{"_":588,"target":589},"ISic001400","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001400",{"type":591,"xml:lang":200,"resp":479,"p":592},"translation","To the underworld spirits. Agathopous, worthy man, farewell! You lived ---.",{"type":591,"xml:lang":403,"resp":479,"p":594},"Agli Dei inferi. Illustre Agathopos, salve! Hai vissuto ---.",{"type":596,"resp":479,"p":597},"commentary",[598,624,638],{"_":599,"foreign":600,"ref":611},"According to Korhonen, the sequence  can be a contracted abbreviation for  or a linguistic interference from the Latin formula  (the Greek translation would be , cf. IG 14, no.476 = ). The deceased's name in vocative, the imperative form  and a verb 'to live' in the second-person singular form followed by the age is a formula, which recurs in other inscriptions of Catania, cf. IG 14, no.469 = , IG 14, no.493 = , IG 14, no.497a =  and of the nearby Centuripe (cf. Korhonen 2004: 84-85).",[601,603,605,607,609],{"_":602,"xml:lang":120},"ΘΚΣ",{"_":604,"xml:lang":120},"Θεοῖς Κατακθονίοις",{"_":606,"xml:lang":407},"D(iis) M(anibus) S(acrum)",{"_":608,"xml:lang":120},"Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)",{"_":610,"xml:lang":120},"χαῖρε",[612,615,618,621],{"_":613,"target":614},"ISic001299","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001299",{"_":616,"target":617},"ISic001293","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001293",{"_":619,"target":620},"ISic001315","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001315",{"_":622,"target":623},"ISic001319","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001319",{"_":625,"foreign":626,"ref":633},"The epithet  is frequently referred to the deceased in Catania (IG 14, no.482 = , IG 14, no.493 = ), even if the most frequent formula is . The proper name  is attested also in inscriptions from Syracuse, Tauromenion and Thermai Himeraiai (LGPN 3A: 5).",[627,629,631],{"_":628,"xml:lang":120},"χρηστός",{"_":630,"xml:lang":120},"χρηστὸς καὶ ἄμεμπτος",{"_":632,"xml:lang":120},"Ἀγαθόπους",[634,637],{"_":635,"target":636},"ISic001305","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001305",{"_":619,"target":620},"The inscription is most likely from Catania, but the formula is also attested at Centuripe, and as Korhonen notes inscriptions from other locations such as Centuripe entered the Biscari collection during the period in which this was apparently found (between the first and second editions of Torremuzza's corpus).",{"type":640,"listBibl":641},"bibliography",[642,666],{"type":122,"bibl":643},[644,649,652,657,660,663],{"author":125,"date":126,"citedRange":645,"ptr":647,"ref":648},{"ref":646},{"_":129,"target":130},{"target":132},{"_":134,"target":134},{"author":136,"date":137,"citedRange":138,"ptr":650,"ref":651},{"target":140},{"_":142,"target":142},{"type":144,"n":145,"citedRange":653,"ptr":655,"ref":656},{"ref":654},{"_":148,"target":149},{"target":151},{"_":153,"target":153},{"type":144,"n":155,"citedRange":156,"ptr":658,"ref":659},{"target":158},{"_":160,"target":160},{"type":144,"n":162,"citedRange":163,"ptr":661,"ref":662},{"target":165},{"_":167,"target":167},{"type":144,"n":169,"citedRange":170,"ptr":664,"ref":665},{"target":172},{"_":174,"target":174},{"type":176,"bibl":667},[668,182],{"type":144,"n":155,"citedRange":179,"ptr":669,"ref":670},{"target":158},{"_":160,"target":160},[672,673,674,675],{"n":486,"url":104,"width":487,"height":488,"desc":105,"surfaceType":483},{"n":486,"url":493,"width":494,"height":495,"desc":496,"surfaceType":483},{"n":486,"url":500,"width":501,"height":502,"desc":496,"surfaceType":483},{"n":486,"url":509,"width":487,"height":488,"desc":105,"surfaceType":506},{"title":677,"body":678,"divs":679,"images":695},"ISic001282. Epitaph of Agathopous","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr1_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001282_fr1_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr1.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001282_fr1-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr2_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale &quot;M. M. Lazzaro&quot; di Catania\" src=\"ISic001282_fr2_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr2.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale &quot;M. M. Lazzaro&quot; di Catania\" src=\"ISic001282_fr2-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr3_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale &quot;M. M. Lazzaro&quot; di Catania\" src=\"ISic001282_fr3_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr3.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photograph by Liceo Artistico Statale &quot;M. M. Lazzaro&quot; di Catania\" src=\"ISic001282_fr3-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr1_rev_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001282_fr1_rev_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001282_fr1_rev.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001282_fr1_rev-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Θivy-leafΚΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΑΓΑΘΟΠΟΥΧΡΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΣΤΕ&nbsp;&nbsp;ivy-leaf&nbsp;&nbsp;Χ..ΡΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>...[......\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Castelli, Franz: Θ Κ; Ferrara: Θ Κ I; Kaibel Θ Κ Σ (i.e. Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοι)ς)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Franz: ἔζη[σας ἔτη]; Kaibel: ἔζη[σεν ἔτη]; Korhonen: ἔζη[σας ἔτη] (or ἔζη[σες ἔτη], frequent in Centuripe, see IG 14, no.578 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001397\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001397\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.579 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001398\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001398\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.581 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001400\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001400\u003C/a>)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Agathopous, worthy man, farewell! You lived ---.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Illustre Agathopos, salve! Hai vissuto ---.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>According to Korhonen, the sequence \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ΘΚΣ\u003C/span> can be a contracted abbreviation for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοῖς Κατακθονίοις\u003C/span> or a linguistic interference from the Latin formula \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">D(iis) M(anibus) S(acrum)\u003C/span> (the Greek translation would be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)\u003C/span>, cf. IG 14, no.476 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001299\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001299\u003C/a>). The deceased's name in vocative, the imperative form \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χαῖρε\u003C/span> and a verb 'to live' in the second-person singular form followed by the age is a formula, which recurs in other inscriptions of Catania, cf. IG 14, no.469 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001293\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001293\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.493 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001315\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001315\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.497a = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001319\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001319\u003C/a> and of the nearby Centuripe (cf. Korhonen 2004: 84-85).\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>The epithet \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστός\u003C/span> is frequently referred to the deceased in Catania (IG 14, no.482 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001305\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001305\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.493 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001315\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001315\u003C/a>), even if the most frequent formula is \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστὸς καὶ ἄμεμπτος\u003C/span>. The proper name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἀγαθόπους\u003C/span> is attested also in inscriptions from Syracuse, Tauromenion and Thermai Himeraiai (LGPN 3A: 5).\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>The inscription is most likely from Catania, but the formula is also attested at Centuripe, and as Korhonen notes inscriptions from other locations such as Centuripe entered the Biscari collection during the period in which this was apparently found (between the first and second editions of Torremuzza's corpus).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> Castelli 1784 \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/501873\" target=\"_blank\">170 cl.14 no.5\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 348 n.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">14.0458\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 53 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 3.5696 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001252\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 5240 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 84-85 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[680,682,684,686,688,690,692],{"id":122,"html":681},"\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div\">\u003Ca id=\"al1\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Θivy-leafΚΣ\u003Cbr id=\"al2\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΑΓΑΘΟΠΟΥΧΡΗ\u003Cbr id=\"al3\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΣΤΕ&nbsp;&nbsp;ivy-leaf&nbsp;&nbsp;Χ..ΡΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al4\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>...[......\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"id":568,"html":683},"\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">line.1: \u003Cspan>Castelli, Franz: Θ Κ; Ferrara: Θ Κ I; Kaibel Θ Κ Σ (i.e. Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοι)ς)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Franz: ἔζη[σας ἔτη]; Kaibel: ἔζη[σεν ἔτη]; Korhonen: ἔζη[σας ἔτη] (or ἔζη[σες ἔτη], frequent in Centuripe, see IG 14, no.578 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001397\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001397\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.579 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001398\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001398\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.581 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001400\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001400\u003C/a>)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":591,"html":685},"\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Agathopous, worthy man, farewell! You lived ---.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":591,"html":687},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Illustre Agathopos, salve! Hai vissuto ---.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":596,"html":689},"\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>According to Korhonen, the sequence \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ΘΚΣ\u003C/span> can be a contracted abbreviation for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θεοῖς Κατακθονίοις\u003C/span> or a linguistic interference from the Latin formula \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">D(iis) M(anibus) S(acrum)\u003C/span> (the Greek translation would be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)\u003C/span>, cf. IG 14, no.476 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001299\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001299\u003C/a>). The deceased's name in vocative, the imperative form \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χαῖρε\u003C/span> and a verb 'to live' in the second-person singular form followed by the age is a formula, which recurs in other inscriptions of Catania, cf. IG 14, no.469 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001293\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001293\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.493 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001315\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001315\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.497a = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001319\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001319\u003C/a> and of the nearby Centuripe (cf. Korhonen 2004: 84-85).\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>The epithet \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστός\u003C/span> is frequently referred to the deceased in Catania (IG 14, no.482 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001305\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001305\u003C/a>, IG 14, no.493 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001315\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001315\u003C/a>), even if the most frequent formula is \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστὸς καὶ ἄμεμπτος\u003C/span>. The proper name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Ἀγαθόπους\u003C/span> is attested also in inscriptions from Syracuse, Tauromenion and Thermai Himeraiai (LGPN 3A: 5).\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>The inscription is most likely from Catania, but the formula is also attested at Centuripe, and as Korhonen notes inscriptions from other locations such as Centuripe entered the Biscari collection during the period in which this was apparently found (between the first and second editions of Torremuzza's corpus).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":640,"html":691},"\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \